    "heroSummary": "Many Asana automations follow one operational path: a form, CRM, or internal system creates tasks in a project, places them in the right section, assigns a user, and fills custom fields.\n\nThe trouble starts later, when comments, attachments, subtasks, or completion state are supposed to drive updates in another system and the workflow is relying on ambiguous searches, project selection quirks, or polling inside a busy workspace.",
