    "introSummary": "Many teams use Google Sheets as the source table for lead, request, or ticket records, then rely on Microsoft Outlook to send an email or create a draft when a row changes in one worksheet.\n\nThe reverse pattern is common too: a new Outlook message in a personal inbox or shared mailbox is logged into Google Sheets for tracking. That setup works for light internal use, but it becomes unreliable when worksheet structure, folder scope, and Microsoft connection state start changing during normal operations.",
