    "problemSummary": "This workflow usually degrades through small operating changes rather than one obvious outage. A Google Sheets worksheet used as the source table for lead, request, or ticket records may be renamed, reordered, or have headers edited. Once that happens, the row data mapped into Microsoft Outlook can shift without much warning because the automation depends on one worksheet and one row schema, not on every change across all spreadsheets, sheets, rows, ranges, and cells.\n\nThe Outlook side fails differently.",
