    "heroSummary": "Many teams use Zapier to watch a Gmail account: a free or paid Gmail mailbox connected to Zapier, then send matching email details into a Slack workspace/channel.\n\nTrouble starts when that flow handles support escalations, invoice review, or shared inbox triage, because Gmail polling, label or search rules, thread handling, and Slack channel routing all need tighter control than a simple Zap usually provides.",
