    "replacementSummary": "A direct Google Sheets and Mailchimp integration should treat the spreadsheet as a controlled source table, not just a trigger. It should define which spreadsheets, sheets, rows, ranges, and cells are in scope, validate the required headers before each run, and check that each row has a usable email, an allowed status, and the fields needed for the target audience. It should also separate create, update, skip, and review decisions so a bulk cleanup in Sheets does not silently rewrite Mailchimp in the wrong way.\n\nOn the Mailchimp side, the workflow should target the correct audience every time, because Mailchimp audiences function independently and do not share data.",
