      "problem_heading": "Why this Google Sheets and Typeform workflow stops feeling reliable",
      "problem_summary": "The expected behavior sounds simple: a respondent submits a Typeform and a new row should appear in the connected Google Sheet tab. In practice, trust usually breaks through pair-specific edge cases. A partial submit point can create an earlier row before the final one. A reused spreadsheet can fail because the destination already has a tab with the same name as the form. An existing file can also fail at setup if it was not shared correctly before connection. Once teams start relying on the spreadsheet for real decisions, those details matter more than the basic promise of row creation.",
