      "problem_heading": "Why Shopify customer sync into Google Contacts becomes hard to trust",
      "problem_summary": "The trouble here usually builds through ordinary customer changes. A Shopify store creates a contact for a first purchase, then the same customer updates a phone number, adds a company name, changes marketing preference fields, or places another paid order that should affect segmentation. If the process does not preserve a stable link between the Shopify customer ID and the Google Contacts destination, later runs can create duplicates, overwrite the wrong contact, leave an outdated Google Contacts group assignment, or skip an update entirely.",
